		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Megaman 9 (an maybe other) metatile format</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />While looking at mega man 9 concrete man map that someone made <a href="http://vgmaps.com/Atlas/Wii/MegaMan9-ConcreteMan.png" class="postlink">here</a> I started to ask myself what kind of metatile they could have used (that must be one of the side effects of the nesdev "virus" I guess <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />).
<br />
<br />My first impression was that they could have used a 4x4 metatile then made metatile out of metatile. But when you look at the patterns...  In general it could be fine but in some case you would have to make redundant meta-metatile just for some specific area.  
<br />
<br />I guess it's not that much an interesting question but what do people think about it?  What kind of metatile mega man 9 or other mega man game uses in general?  As it always been the same?  I'm curious.  My guess is now on the 4x4 metatile only, no meta-metatile.
<br />
<br />I should just play the $#%! game and stop checking those details... <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


