	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think you are right about the 4x4 metatiles, and it seems they are arranged in "screens", since the path is always 1 screen tall or 1 screen wide. I'd guess that each screen is individually encoded, but it appers they can't be considered metatiles themselves, as it seems they are not reused in different parts of the level.
<br />
<br />On the other hand, since this game was not made to run on a system with severe memory limitations, it might very well have the levels stored in a very straightforward not compressed format just mimicking the overall look of it's predecessors, which for sure used metatile-based compression. Someone would have to reverse engineer the game and check, I guess.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


